node.text:
Parker’s recovery 
(Parker had two masses removed a couple of weeks ago and it was one of the most stressful times waiting for the results to see if they were cancerous or not. Luckily they weren’t, and Parker is recovering. Yay! )

#illustration #iloveparker

node.text:
Where the currents take me

(Hope you guys are having a better year so far! At the end of last year I told myself to take it easy in 2021. Well... somehow I’m busier now than ever🙃. I signed up for a few classes, took on some projects, and now I’m struggling once again to find the time to do my own illustrations. But it’s ok, it’s been fun trying out different things.) #illustration

node.text:
Almost Christmas🎄 

(This year is wrapping up! I really hope we all have a much better 2021. It’s been a rough year to say the least! 
I’ve been stuck in a constant cycle of stress and anxiety, as I’m sure most of you can relate to. One of the many things I’ve been stressed out about is worrying I’m not growing as an artist. I love drawing Parker, but sometimes I feel stuck. I’ve decided that next year I’m going to focus on learning and force myself to practice different areas of art that I’m lacking in (which is a Lot). I’ll still draw Parker, but don’t be surprised if I draw other things too. Hopefully it’s not too embarrassingly bad hehehe 

Anyway, thank you all for being on my art journey so far, and I hope to see you guys on next year’s journey as well! Please stay safe, and I wish you all an extra happy holidays this year! 🥰😊) #illustration #happyholidays

node.text:
The better spot 

( I haven’t had much time to work on personal work recently, but I’ve been chipping away at this one, trying to learn how to use harmony. I had to leave out Parker’s brindle because it would’ve taken too long lol 🥲) 

#illustration #toonboomharmony

node.text:
Chilling with Parker #illustration #autumn 

Well, I’m stressed lol. Each year I look forward to drawing autumn leading up to Halloween stuff because it’s my favorite time of year. Without fail, all my deadlines always end up converging around the same time, making it impossible to draw regularly. The longer I go without drawing, the more stressed out I feel about not spending time improving myself as an artist. I’m making next year all about learning😊
